The <strong><code>Function</code> constructor</strong> creates a new <code>Function</code> object. Calling the constructor directly can create functions dynamically, but suffers fromÂ security and similar (but far less significant) performance issues to <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/eval" title="REDIRECT eval()"><code>eval</code></a>. However, unlike eval, the Function constructor creates functions which execute in the global scope only.